perl-module-build: perl-module-build (Alternative Perl-Module build system)
perl-module-build:
perl-module-build: 'Module::Build' is a system for building, testing, and installing
perl-module-build: Perl modules. It is meant to be an alternative to
perl-module-build: 'ExtUtils::MakeMaker'. Developers may alter the behavior of the
perl-module-build: module through subclassing in a much more straightforward way than
perl-module-build: with 'MakeMaker'. It also does not require a 'make' on your system
perl-module-build: - most of the 'Module::Build' code is pure-perl and written in a
perl-module-build: very cross-platform way.
perl-module-build:
